The paper deals with graph-based submodular maximization problems, which are typically studied in the areas of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), social and information networks (cs.SI), machine learning (cs.LG), social and economic systems (cs.SOC), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper's focus on influence functions and their applications in viral marketing, monitoring, and active learning of node labels suggests that it is likely to be classified under these sub-categories.
